    {# ----- Furniture: VR ----- #}

    <p>
        Most of my time was spent exploring how a &#60;model&#62; element and new 3D CSS properties might work. I created a series of animations (below) and prototypes (not shown) which played with, among other things: cropping when models exceeded their bounding boxes; responsive interfaces across mobile, VR, and AR; coordinate systems; and real world use cases. Most of the animations were created in Cinema 4D. I made heavy use of the built-in scripting engine, XPresso, to help automate otherwise laborious manual keyframing. It enabled me to build complex hierarchies of interconnected animation values, exposed as simple UI sliders and toggles.
    </p>

